<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=12250&amp;p=139744#p139744"><![CDATA[
Verdict:<br /><br />1) The fan inside the case was reverted! It was corrected to flow the air from inside to outside.<br />2) The thermal paste was gone. New paste was applied.<br />3) The heatsink was loose. It's fixed.<br />4) One cable had bad placement inside the case.<br /><br />The PC is working like a charm. ^_^;;<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=39">Zepper</a> — Wed Jan 21, 2015 7:01 pm</p><hr />
