<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=12250&amp;p=139273#p139273</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=12250&amp;p=139273#p139273"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: PC overheat?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=12250&amp;p=139273#p139273"><![CDATA[
When the CPU temperature rises, modern CPUs will try to underclock themselves (=&gt; slowdown) to keep the temperature within limits. In case the temperature still manages to reach a certain threshold, it will shut itself down as a safety measure.<br /><br />Try cleaning your CPU fan with compressed air and make sure it's properly seated. Some diagnostic applications can be useful in finding out the CPU frequency and temperature.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=80">thefox</a> — Thu Jan 15, 2015 8:34 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
